    "id": "cardiology-102",
    "system": "Cardiology",
    "topic": "Mobitz I heart block management",
    "stem": "A routine ECG in an asymptomatic 45-year-old shows progressive lengthening of the PR interval until a QRS complex is dropped, after which the cycle repeats. Which of the following is the most appropriate management?",
