      "Cerebral edema occurs with hyponatremia itself, not days after correction, and his sodium is now higher.",
      "Correct: rapid correction (>8-10 mEq/L/24h) of chronic hyponatremia causes osmotic demyelination, classically delayed by 1-several days.",
