    "concept": "Sodium correction rate should not exceed 8-10 mEq/L in 24 hours (even less in chronic, severe, or malnourished/alcoholic patients) to avoid osmotic demyelination syndrome. If overcorrection occurs, some experts advocate re-lowering sodium with desmopressin and free water.",
