    "topic": "ECG changes of hyperkalemia",
    "stem": "A 60-year-old man with end-stage renal disease misses two dialysis sessions and presents with weakness. Serum potassium is 7.2 mEq/L. ECG shows peaked T waves and a widened QRS complex. Which of the following is the most appropriate immediate next step?",
