      "Dialysis is definitive therapy in ESRD but takes time to arrange; calcium must be given first to prevent arrhythmia in the interim.",
      "Correct: calcium stabilizes the cardiac membrane immediately and is the first step whenever ECG changes accompany hyperkalemia.",
      "Insulin/glucose shifts potassium intracellularly but does not protect the myocardium and takes longer to act than calcium.",
