    "concept": "Reperfusion therapy has two separate windows: IV thrombolysis is generally limited to 4.5 hours from last known well, while mechanical thrombectomy for large-vessel occlusion can extend to 24 hours in patients selected by perfusion imaging showing a small infarct core with substantial salvageable penumbra.",
