    "concept": "Morning hyperglycemia in an insulin-treated diabetic can result from either the Somogyi phenomenon (nocturnal hypoglycemia with rebound hyperglycemia, confirmed by low 3 AM glucose) or the dawn phenomenon (early-morning surge of counter-regulatory hormones without preceding hypoglycemia). Checking a 3 AM glucose distinguishes the two and dictates opposite management.",
