    "concept": "Compartment syndrome is diagnosed by clinical findings supported by compartment pressure measurement, typically using a delta pressure (diastolic BP minus compartment pressure) threshold of less than 30 mmHg. Once diagnosed, emergent fasciotomy is required to prevent muscle necrosis, contractures, and limb loss."
