    "stem": "A 68-year-old man reports bilateral leg and buttock pain when walking down a hill or standing at the sink for more than 10 minutes. The pain is relieved by sitting down or leaning forward on a shopping cart. Peripheral pulses are normal and there is no history of cardiovascular disease. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?",
