      "Neurogenic claudication with positional relief on flexion and normal pulses is the hallmark of lumbar spinal stenosis.",
      "Disc herniation causes unilateral radiculopathy following an inciting movement, not bilateral position-dependent claudication.",
      "Vascular claudication is reproducible with any exertion regardless of posture and is associated with diminished pulses, both absent here.",
