    "concept": "Lumbar spinal stenosis is degenerative narrowing of the spinal canal in patients typically over 50, producing neurogenic claudication that worsens with standing/extension and improves with sitting/flexion. Peripheral pulses remain normal, distinguishing it from vascular claudication.",
