    "topic": "Specificity interpretation",
    "stem": "A study is conducted to determine whether a hemoglobin A1c greater than 15% predicts diabetic retinopathy. Results show that 88% of all patients without diabetic retinopathy had a hemoglobin A1c below 15%. Which of the following is the most accurate interpretation of these results?",
