    "concept": "Positive predictive value (PPV) is highly sensitive to disease prevalence (pretest probability): as prevalence falls, PPV falls even for a test with excellent sensitivity and specificity, because the absolute number of false positives from the much larger disease-free population overwhelms the true positives from the small diseased population. This is why screening tests in low-prevalence populations require careful pretest probability assessment before ordering.",
