    "stem": "A 37-year-old woman in a long-term mutually monogamous relationship returns for a second opinion about a positive Chlamydia trachomatis test and disbelieves the result. The prevalence of C. trachomatis in her age group is less than 1%, the test sensitivity is 80%, and the specificity is 97%. Which of the following parameters best explains the validity of her positive result?",
