    "topic": "Alcoholic hallucinosis timing",
    "stem": "A 55-year-old man with a history of heavy daily alcohol use presents 24 hours after his last drink reporting that he feels bugs crawling on his skin. His vital signs are normal, and he is oriented to person, place, and time. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?",
