      "Wernicke encephalopathy presents with confusion, ataxia, and ophthalmoplegia, not isolated tactile hallucinations.",
      "Correct: tactile hallucinations at 12-48 hours with normal orientation and vitals define alcoholic hallucinosis.",
      "Korsakoff syndrome presents with anterograde amnesia and confabulation, not acute hallucinations.",
      "Delirium tremens occurs later (2-4 days) and features autonomic instability and confusion, not present here."
