    "concept": "Alcoholic hallucinosis occurs 12-48 hours after the last drink, typically with tactile or visual hallucinations but preserved orientation and normal vital signs, distinguishing it from the more dangerous delirium tremens that occurs 2-4 days later.",
    "discriminator": "Preserved orientation and normal vital signs distinguish alcoholic hallucinosis from delirium tremens, which features disorientation and autonomic instability."
