    "id": "mental-17",
    "system": "Mental Disorders",
    "topic": "Delirium vs dementia",
    "stem": "A 78-year-old man is 2 days post-hip fracture repair. Over the past 12 hours he has become agitated, is picking at his IV line, and cannot maintain attention during conversation. His mental status fluctuates throughout the day, worse at night. He had no cognitive complaints before surgery. Which of the following best characterizes this presentation?",
